  "texts": [
    "In this section, we will describe the landmark work in detail.",
    "The KNN-LM approach involves linearly interpolating the extended neural language model with the K-Nearest Neighbours in the pre-trained LM embedding space.",
    "Zhong et al. (2022) proposed different processing for three types of memories (local, long-term and external) and added training for in-batch tokens to KNN-LM.",
    "The proposed changes aim to improve the performance of the model.",
    "Unlike KNN-LM, which only uses memory units during training, TRIME (Zhong et al., 2022) uses memory units during both testing and training."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Zhong et al. (2022) proposed different processing for three types of memories (local, long-term and external) and added training for in-batch tokens to KNN-LM.",
    "Unlike KNN-LM, which only uses memory units during training, TRIME (Zhong et al., 2022) uses memory units during both testing and training."
